Peer pressure can be defined as a great and powerful force that can shape our decisions and action. It is also the influence exerted by one's social gatherings or peers to conform to certain behaviours, attitudes or values thet may or may not align with Religious teachings.
Islamic perspective:                                                      influence of the companions, evaluation, avoidance of sins
Real-life sceneroes: Drug abuse, academic dishonesty, social media, bullying
positive peer pressure:surrounding oneself witth righteous people, It increase acts of charity, encourages righteous behaviour
negative impact: behaviuors that contradicts one religion, neglecting prayers or fasting, participation in unlawful activities
guidance on resisting peer pressure: developing self-confidfence, surround yourself with righteous people,seek guidance from righteous leaders.
key concepts: god consciousness, worship, reliance on Allah.  